      <cite class='section'>HL Deb 22 July 2004 vol 664 c48WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_48ws' title='Col. 48WS &mdash; HL Deb 22 July 2004 vol 664 c48WS' name='column_48ws' href='#column_48ws' rel='bookmark'>48WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0664P0-10744'>
        <a name='S5LV0664P0_20040722_LWS_16'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/ms-patricia-scotland' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0664P0_20040722_LWS_16' title='Link to this speech by Ms Patricia Scotland' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/ms-patricia-scotland" title="Ms Patricia Scotland">Baroness Scotland of Asthal</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S5LV0664P0-10744">I am today announcing that the Charity Commission will be publishing its departmental report for 2004 on 23 July. Copies of that report will be available in the Library.</p>
        </blockquote>
